label.value: regulation of bundle of His cell action potential

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination in a cardiac muscle cell of the bundle of His. This typically occurs via modulation of the activity or expression of voltage-gated ion channels.

label.value: regulation of Purkinje myocyte action potential

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination in a Purkinje myocyte. This typically occurs via modulation of the activity or expression of voltage-gated ion channels.

label.value: regulation of SA node cell action potential

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination in an SA node cardiac myocyte. This typically occurs via modulation of the activity or expression of voltage-gated ion channels.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination in a neuron. This typically occurs via modulation of the activity or expression of voltage-gated ion channels.

label.value: regulation of cardiac muscle cell action potential involved in regulation of contraction

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination in a cardiac muscle cell contributing to the regulation of its contraction.

label.value: regulation of atrial cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination in an atrial cardiac muscle cell contributing to the regulation of its contraction. This typically occurs via modulation of the activity or expression of voltage-gated ion channels.

label.value: regulation of ventricular cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination in a ventricular cardiac muscle cell contributing to the regulation of its contraction. This typically occurs via modulation of the activity or expression of voltage-gated ion channels.

label.value: membrane depolarization during atrial cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: The process in which atrial cardiac muscle cell membrane potential changes in the depolarizing direction from the negative resting potential towards the positive membrane potential that will be the peak of the action potential.

label.value: membrane depolarization during ventricular cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: The process in which ventricular cardiac muscle cell membrane potential changes in the depolarizing direction from the negative resting potential towards the positive membrane potential that will be the peak of the action potential.

label.value: membrane repolarization during atrial cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: The process in which ions are transported across a membrane such that the atrial cardiomyocyte membrane potential changes in the direction from the positive membrane potential at the peak of the action potential towards the negative resting potential.

label.value: membrane repolarization during ventricular cardiac muscle cell action potential

value.value: The process in which ions are transported across a membrane such that the ventricular cardiomyocyte membrane potential changes in the direction from the positive membrane potential at the peak of the action potential towards the negative resting potential.
Cell-cell signaling from pre to post-synapse, across the synaptic cleft.
Cell-cell signaling from post to pre-synapse, across the synaptic cleft.
The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of a synapse.
The action of a molecule that contributes to the structural integrity of a postsynaptic density.
Cell-cell signaling from postsynapse to presynapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by a lipid ligand.
Cell-cell signaling from postsynapse to presynapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by an endocannabinoid ligand.

label.value: extrinsic component of dense core granule membrane

value.value: The component of the dense core granule membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that are loosely bound to one of its surfaces, but not integrated into the hydrophobic region.

label.value: retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by soluble gas

value.value: Cell-cell signaling from postsynapse to presynapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by an soluble gas ligand.

label.value: retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by nitric oxide

value.value: Cell-cell signaling from postsynapse to presynapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by nitric oxide.

label.value: retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by nitric oxide, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Modulation of synaptic transmission by cell-cell signaling from postsynapse to presynapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by nitric oxide.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Signal transduction in which the initial step occurs in a postsynapse.
A cellular transport process in which transported substances are moved in membrane-bounded vesicles between endosomal compartments, e.g, between early endosome and sorting endosome.
Signal transduction in which the initial step occurs in a presynapse.
The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in axons.

label.value: virion attachment to host cell flagellum

value.value: The process by which a virion attaches to a the host cell flagellum. Some DNA bacterial viruses use flagella to attach to the host cell. This contact with the flagellum facilitates concentration of phage particles around the entry receptor on the bacterial cell surface.

label.value: symbiont entry into host cell via disruption of host cell wall peptidoglycan

value.value: The disruption by a symbiont of host cell wall peptidoglycans to allow entry into the host cell.

label.value: symbiont-mediated disruption of host cell envelope

value.value: The process in which a symbiont effects a change that impairs the structure or function of the host cell envelope. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.
The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in a dendrite from the postsynapse towards the cell body.
The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in dendrites.
The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules from the cell body toward the postsynapse in dendrites.
The actin cytoskeleton that is part of a dendritic spine.
The directed movement of mitochondria along microtubules in nerve cell dendrites.

label.value: anterograde trans-synaptic signaling by nitric oxide

value.value: Cell-cell signaling from presynapse to postynapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by nitric oxide.

label.value: anterograde trans-synaptic signaling by trans-synaptic protein complex

value.value: Cell-cell signaling from presynapse to postynapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by a trans-synaptic protein complex.

label.value: retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by trans-synaptic protein complex

value.value: Cell-cell signaling from postsynapse to presynapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by trans-synaptic protein complex.

label.value: neurotransmitter receptor transport, postsynaptic endosome to lysosome

value.value: The directed movement of neurotransmitter receptor from the postsynaptic endosome in tranpsort vesicles to the lysosome for degradation.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a postsynaptic recycling endosome.

The process by which a membrane receptor, diffusing freely within the plasma membeane, becomes trapped in some plasma membrane region. This can happen when a receptor bind, directly or indirectly, to some component of the underlying matrix.
The lipid bilayer surrounding a presynaptic endosome.
The directed movement of mitochondria along microtubules in axons away from the cell body and towards the presynapse.
The directed movement of mitochondria along microtubules in axons towards the cell body and away from the presynapse.
The directed movement of mitochondria along microtubules in dendrites towards the cell body and away from the postsynapse.
Neurotransmitter receptor activity occurring in the postsynaptic membrane during synaptic transmission.
The directed movement of a ribonucleoprotein complex along microtubules in nerve cell dendrites.

label.value: regulation of postsynaptic neurotransmitter receptor activity

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neurotransmitter receptor activity involved in synaptic transmission. Modulation may be via an effect on ligand affinity, or effector function such as ion selectivity or pore opening/closing in ionotropic receptors.

label.value: dendritic transport of messenger ribonucleoprotein complex

value.value: The directed movement of a messenger ribonucleoprotein complex along microtubules in nerve cell dendrites.

label.value: anterograde dendritic transport of messenger ribonucleoprotein complex

value.value: The directed movement of a messenger ribonucleoprotein complex along microtubules in nerve cell dendrites towards the postsynapse.
The portion of the extracellular matrix that lies within the synaptic cleft.
The portion of the extracellular matrix that lies within the perisynaptic space.
